Class FileType<T>

java.lang.Object
com.dua3.utility.io.FileType<T>
Type Parameters:

public abstract class FileType<T> extends Object implements Comparable<FileType<?>>
A class representing files of a certain type.

    • isCompound

      public boolean isCompound()
      Whether this is a compound file type (a wrapper for different filetypes having common properties).

      NOTE: Compound file types are excluded when looking up a file type by supported extensions.

      Some file types are used in dialogs to group together different other types that have common properties, i.e., "All supported files" of an application. These compound file types can be useful to offer a better user experience but are not suitable for determining in what file format data should be written (an example being "Excel files" which refers to both XLS and XLSX files).

      Returns:
      if this file type is a compound file type
